🏗️ The System Architecture: "The Smart Agency Funnel"
​Your system is designed to solve three major South African problems: High volume (junk) apps, manual formatting waste, and paper-based walk-ins.
​1. The Command Center (Agency Dashboard)
​The agency doesn't just "post a job." They create a Requirement DNA.
​The Inputs: The recruiter enters mandatory skills (e.g., "Code 14 License"), years of experience, and location.
​The Logic: They set a "Scoring Threshold" (e.g., 75%).
​The Brand Setup: They upload their logo and choose their "Agency Signature" colors. This ensures every CV generated by the system looks like it was made by a professional design firm.
​2. The Multi-Channel Intake (The "Vacuum")
​Candidates enter your system through three different doors:
​Door A (The Web Link): Candidates apply via a clean, mobile-friendly URL on their phones.
​Door B (The CV Upload): Candidates upload their existing, messy Word/PDF resumes.
​Door C (The Physical Scan): For walk-ins, the receptionist uses the Mobile OCR Scanner. Your system "reads" the paper, extracts the text using AI (Gemini/Vision API), and digitizes the candidate instantly.
​3. The Processing Engine (The "Brain")
​Once the data is in, the system performs two simultaneous actions:
​Action 1: The Transformation. It strips the "raw" data and pours it into your Premium Agency Template. It removes the candidate’s direct contact info (to protect the agency's commission) and adds the agency’s branding.
​Action 2: The Logic Gate. The AI compares the candidate’s profile against the "Requirement DNA."
​Keyword Analysis: Does "Python" mean the same as "Django Developer" for this role?
​Experience Math: Does the timeline add up to 5 years?
​4. The Automated Sorting (Fast-Track vs. Lobby)
​This is the heart of your value. The system makes a decision so the recruiter doesn't have to:
​🔥 The Fast-Track Folder: Candidates who "Pass." The system can be set to Auto-Email these PDFs directly to the client/institution. The recruiter wakes up to a message: "We found 3 perfect matches; they are already in your client's inbox."
​📥 The Lobby: Candidates who "Fail" or "Almost Pass." They aren't deleted (staying POPIA compliant), but they are hidden from the main view. This keeps the recruiter's screen clean.
​5. The Financial Engine (How You Get Paid)
​This runs in the background to keep you out of debt:
​The Meter: Every time a CV is processed (Web, Upload, or Scan), a "Unit" is consumed.

​6. The Compliance & Security Layer
​POPIA Vault: All data is encrypted. The "Lobby" has an auto-delete timer (e.g., 6 months) to ensure the agency doesn't keep personal data longer than necessary.
​The Audit Log: Every time a CV is sent to an institution, the system logs it. The agency owner can see exactly how much work their recruiters are doing.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         1. Small Agency Plan

Base fee: R2,500/month → gives full access to the system (dashboard, lobbies, templates, reports, OCR, multi-channel intake)

Bonus included CVs: 800 CVs per month

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 800

2. Medium Agency Plan

Base fee: R4,500/month → full platform access

Bonus included CVs: 2,000 CVs per month

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 2,000

3. Large Agency Plan

Base fee: R8,500/month → full platform access

Bonus included CVs: 5,000 CVs per month

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 5,000

4. Enterprise / Massive Organization Plan

Base fee: R12,500/month → full platform access

Bonus included CVs: 10,000 CVs per month

Extra CVs: R2 per CV above 10,000                                                                                                                  🏗️ The Smart Agency Funnel + Pricing
System Overview

Command Center (Agency Dashboard)

Create “Requirement DNA” with mandatory skills, experience, location, scoring threshold.

Upload logo + choose signature colors → every CV looks professionally designed.

Multi-Channel Intake (The Vacuum)

Door A: Web link (mobile-friendly)

Door B: CV Upload (Word/PDF)

Door C: Physical Scan → OCR digitizes paper CVs instantly

Processing Engine (The Brain)

Transformation: Standardizes CVs, removes candidate contact info, adds branding.

Logic Gate: AI scores candidates against Requirement DNA (keyword analysis, experience math).

Automated Sorting

Fast-Track Folder: Perfect matches auto-sent to clients

Lobby: “Almost pass/fail” candidates stored safely (POPIA compliant)

Financial Engine (Meter)

Each CV processed consumes a “unit” → counts toward per-CV fee.

Compliance & Security

POPIA Vault: encrypted data, auto-delete timer

Audit Log: tracks every CV sent

Pricing Plans

1. Small Agency Plan

Base fee: R2,500/month → full system access

Included CVs: 800

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 800

2. Medium Agency Plan

Base fee: R4,500/month → full system access

Included CVs: 2,000

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 2,000

3. Large Agency Plan

Base fee: R8,500/month → full system access

Included CVs: 5,000

Extra CVs: R3 per CV above 5,000

4. Enterprise / Massive Organization Plan

Base fee: R12,500/month → full system access

Included CVs: 10,000

Extra CVs: R2 per CV above 10,000

✅ Key Rules:

Base fee is charged for system access, even if no CVs are processed.

Per-CV fee applies only for CVs processed above the included bonus.

Agencies can pause if they don’t need the system temporarily.

Massive organizations benefit from a lower per-CV fee and high CV allowance.















